The city of Cape has offered a R50 000 reward for the arrest of suspects who allegedly shot a metro office while responding to a smash-and-grab criminal act in the Western Cape, metro police spokesperson JP Smith said today.Constable Siyabonga Minnie was shot and wounded along the Jakes Gerwel Drive yesterday.According to reports, Minnie was wounded when she responded to a smash-and-grab incident along the N2. He was shot in the leg, and is reportedly in a stable condition in hospital.The suspects fled with his service pistol,&#8221; the police said.-TNA Reporter 